**Prompt**

Write a program that reads a string of characters user inputs and removes all whitespace characters and
prints the string back without the whitespace characters. Use getchar().

**Solution**

#include "pch.h"
#include <iostream>
#include <stdio.h>

//this code creates a program that reads 
//a string. It removes all whitespace and
//prints that to the console

int main(void)
{
	//initializes input
	int input;

	//asks user for some words
	printf("Please input some words:\n");

	//removes spaces from user input and prints it
	//back to the terminal
	while (input = getchar()) {
		if (input != ' ') {
			putchar(input);
		}
	}

	return 0;
}
